Description: Corroded fragment of a copper alloy chain made of three twisted eight-shaped links, one broken.
Curator's comments: Possibly part of the bronze "chain of O and of 8 links" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80. But see also London, BM, EA 23902.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.79-80, p.185, pl.27)
